      <title>The Spin Hamiltonian - Part 1</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/nasa_derive_1/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 06 Jun 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/nasa_derive_1/</guid>
      <description>&lt;link rel=&#34;stylesheet&#34; href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/katex/katex.min.css&#34; /&gt;&lt;script defer src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/katex/katex.min.js&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&lt;script defer src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/katex/auto-render.min.js&#34; onload=&#34;renderMathInElement(document.body, {&amp;#34;delimiters&amp;#34;:[{&amp;#34;left&amp;#34;:&amp;#34;$$&amp;#34;,&amp;#34;right&amp;#34;:&amp;#34;$$&amp;#34;,&amp;#34;display&amp;#34;:true},{&amp;#34;left&amp;#34;:&amp;#34;$&amp;#34;,&amp;#34;right&amp;#34;:&amp;#34;$&amp;#34;,&amp;#34;display&amp;#34;:false},{&amp;#34;left&amp;#34;:&amp;#34;\\(&amp;#34;,&amp;#34;right&amp;#34;:&amp;#34;\\)&amp;#34;,&amp;#34;display&amp;#34;:false},{&amp;#34;left&amp;#34;:&amp;#34;\\[&amp;#34;,&amp;#34;right&amp;#34;:&amp;#34;\\]&amp;#34;,&amp;#34;display&amp;#34;:true}]});&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote class=&#34;book-hint warning&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This post is math heavy. I&amp;rsquo;ll try to walk through it all elegantly though. The&#xA;important equations are boxed if you&amp;rsquo;d like to skip through. On mobile some&#xA;equations may go overfull.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;br&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The Spin Hamiltonian $\mathscr{H}$ governs the spin-physics of recombination. It&amp;rsquo;s what we&#xA;need to program before starting to simulate EDMR.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;$ \mathscr{H} $ is a combination of the Zeeman Effect, Hyperfine Interactions,&#xA;the Zero-field Splitting Effect, and the Exchange Interaction.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
